    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-09-07T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-09-07T18:00:00-05:00" n="61"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d61">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">715.1715/559: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Castleman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-09-07T17:00:00-06:00"
                            >September 7, 1937—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 8:42 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>100. Referring to my telegram No. 98, the Honduran Minister’s statement of
                    assurances will appear in tomorrow morning’s Managua newspapers, which are on
                    the streets tonight, there being no evening papers, accompanied by an expression
                    of gratification by the President of Nicaragua.</p>
                <p>No mention of American action will appear.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Tegucigalpa.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Castleman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
